  <original-body>It's impossible to automatically generate a label for a radio button using a form helper.  The for=&quot;&quot; attribute of a label tag cannot be generated with the same ID of a radio button:

* Radio button ID looks like &quot;model_attribute_value1&quot;
* Label for attribute looks like &quot;model_attribute&quot;

I suggest that the &quot;label&quot; method take an optional value attribute like so:

f.radio_button :attribute, &quot;value1&quot;
f.label :attribute, &quot;Select value1&quot;, :value =&gt; &quot;value1&quot;

Additionally, the code should be refactored so that the code which generates the ID &quot;model_attribute_value1&quot; is only in one place and is consistent.</original-body>
